German Gernot Rohr said the Super Eagles must be wary of the visiting Leone Stars of Sierra Leone as they open their 2013 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) Group An account tomorrow at the Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja. The Super Eagles under Rohr  in 2020, played out two energetic drawn  matches  against the Leone Stars  in the qualifying tournament for the  Cameroon 2021 AFCON  with the game in Benin City ending dramatically  4-4 draw  after  the visitors pulled their chestnuts from the fire  and   bounced from an imminent  4-1 defeat. The second leg in Freetown did not produce a winner either as they both settled for a goalless draw. Today’s meeting will be the 12th between the two West African sides as the Super Eagles aim for their first victory under new coach Jose Peseiro. The Portuguese have recorded two losses in as many friendly matches against Mexico (2-1) and Ecuador (1-0) and Rohr warned the Super Eagles must be ready to a tough task against the battle-hardened Leone Stars who impressed at the Cameroon 2021 after holding both Algeria and Cote d’Ivoire. “The Eagles know that there is no easy game in Africa,” noted the former Bayern Munich defender. “Sierra Leone  made a good AFCON and  cannot be underrated.” Incidentally, the Super Eagles  are searching for their first  win since that 2-0 defeat of  Guinea-Bissau  in their Preliminary  AFCON 2021 Group D at the Stade Roumdé Adjia in Garoua on 19th January. Apart from losing to Tunisia (1-0)  at the AFCON, the Super Eagles drew twice against Black Stars of Ghana  in Qatar 2022 Play-Off ties with a goalless in Tema and a1-1 draw in Abuja  that cost Nigeria the ticket to the Mundial coupled with the  recent losses to Mexico and Ecuador. But Rohr noted the recent setback should be an additional motivation  for the Super eagles to bury the ghost of the visitors. “After five  games without victory, they (super Eagles) should be very hungry to win the match,” noted the former Bordeaux manager.   Nigeria vs: Sierr